  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if vaccination before a structured treatment
      interruption (STI) is associated with an improvement in immune function, resulting in a
      delayed and reduced rebound in the amount of HIV virus in the blood.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Volunteers will be randomly assigned to receive the vaccines or matching placebos before
      interrupting their antiretroviral therapy at week 24.

      Dosage:

      Remune(TM) 1 ml i.m.* at weeks 0, 12, and 20; ALVAC 1 ml i.m.* at weeks 8,12, 16, and 20.

      * i.m.: injected in a muscle
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
